==English==

===Etymology===
From a modern frequentative form of {{m|en|draw}}, equivalent to {{suffix|en|draw|le}}. Compare {{m|en|draggle}}. Compare also {{cog|nl|dralen||to drag out, delay, linger, tarry, dawdle}}, Old Danish {{m|da|dravle||to linger, loiter}}, {{cog|is|dralla||to loiter, linger}}.

